The paper deals with the problem of computing the Walsh-Hadamard Transform (WHT) of a sparse input vector in the presence of noise. This problem is related to signal processing, information theory, and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also proposes a new algorithm that is fast and robust, which suggests that it could belong to cs.SP (Signal Processing) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The algorithm is based on a coding-theoretic design framework, which could also place it in cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.LG (Machine Learning).
